FBIS3-57346 "drsov017_s_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 Georgia Shevardnadze Seeks Tighter Government Management LD2501193794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1744 GMT 25 Jan 94 LD2501193794 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] In a speech to the closed meeting of the parliamentary majority in Tbilisi late on Monday [24 January], Georgian leader Eduard Shevarnadze called to tighten discipline and law enforcement in all tiers of management including parliament, well-informed sources told Interfax. Shevardnadze demanded that parliamentary chief of staff Gamlet Chipashvili be sacked. He blamed the official for failing to include the main point about the country's territorial integrity in a memorandum published in Tbilisi on the results of Georgian-Abkhazian talks in Geneva.
